OL,3,CMinisters have 'no plans' to force
OL,4,Cbusinesses to accept four-day week
OL,5,Cdemands
OL,7,FThe Government has "no plans" to force
OL,8,Fbusinesses to accept employees' four-
OL,9,Fday working week requests.
OL,11,FConservative shadow business secretary
OL,12,FKevin Hollinrake claimed businesses
OL,13,Fwere "petrified" about Labour's Make
OL,14,FWork Pay plans, which The Telegraph
OL,15,Freported could include new rights for
OL,16,Fworkers to demand a four-day week.
OL,18,FBut a Department for Business and
OL,19,FTrade spokesperson denied they would
OL,20,F"impose" the working pattern on
OL,21,Fbusinesses.
