OL,5,Cdemands
OL,7,FIt did not propose a four-day week but
OL,8,Fcommitted the party to banning zero-
OL,9,Fhour contracts, replacing them with
OL,10,Fdocuments which reflect the number of
OL,11,Fhours an employee regularly works, a
OL,12,F"genuine living wage", and an end to
OL,13,F"fire and rehire" practices where
OL,14,Fworkers are laid off and then re-
OL,15,Femployed on new terms.
