OL,3,CMinisters have 'no plans' to force
OL,4,Cbusinesses to accept four-day week
OL,5,Cdemands
OL,7,FThe Telegraph reported "compressed
OL,8,Fhours" could feature in a new law,
OL,9,Fwhich could shift the balance of
OL,10,Fpower, so companies could be legally
OL,11,Fobliged to offer flexible working from
OL,12,Fday one except where it is "not
OL,13,Freasonably feasible".
OL,15,FMr Hollinrake told the newspaper:
OL,16,F"Despite warning after warning from
OL,17,Findustry, Angela Rayner is pressing
OL,18,Fahead with her French-style union laws
OL,19,Fthat will make doing business more
OL,20,Fexpensive in the UK.
